This paper is about recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep learning-based model, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed model uses a capsule routing mechanism, which is a relatively new technique in deep learning and falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of the proposed model in a large-scale industrial setting, which falls under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
